Part 1. Program Description


Part 2. Short Response
Vim related question
1. Type the line number first and then add "G". For example type "20G" in 
   command mode to jump directely to line 20.

2. To turn this on, add this line ":set ai" in command mode.
   To temporarily turn off automatic indenting by typing ":set paste"
   in command mode.

3. Type "u" to undo last change.

4. In command mode, type "b" to move forward one word. Type "w" to move 
   backward one word.

Unix related question
5.Type "rm*.class" to remove all .class files in the directory. 

6.When folder is empty, use "rmdir foldername".

7.Use the command "clear" to clear a unix terminal screen.
